1.name: Spencer Butte Trail
1.description: This [1.7 mile, 741 feet elevation gain] hike is one of the most popular in Eugene, Oregon. Allocate about an 1 hour 20 minutes to complete this adventure and don't forget to take a break and soak up some amazing views once you reach the top.
1.isRain: Yes, for most of the hike you'll be in the forest, so you won't get rained on too hard. Keep in mind that once you get to the top you'll be less likely to spot the amazing views.
1.isSnoworIce: No, this hike has steep, rocky parts that would be dangerous when snow/ice is present

1.name: Float the Willamette River
1.description: Grab your kayak, canoe, floaty, or paddle board and enjoy a relaxing, yet exhilirating excursion down the Willamette River. Drop into the river at West D Boat Ramp (N Willamette St, Eugene, OR 97408) and pop out at River Wood Beach (340 N Adams St, Eugene, OR 97402) for a solid 2 hour float down the river.
1.isRain: No, the water in the river is cold. You will get wet going down this river and we do not reccomend floating down it unless it is sunny and warm.

1.name: Bird Watching at Mt. Pisgah
1.description: Bring your binoculars and enjoy a lovely, relaxing walk here at Mt. Pisgah. This activity requires a $5 pass so please keep that in mind.
1.isRain: Yes, although it might be a little chilly or wet, as long as you're comfortable in a rain jacket this will be a great activity for you.

1.name: Rock Climbing
1.description: Head over to the University of Oregon Rec Center for this one. It's cold, it's raining, maybe it's snowing... all we know is that we are looking for a non-outdoor activity today, and we've got one for you! Head over the the rec center rock wall to spend some time bouldering. Luckily for you (if you're a student) this wall is totally free and you can even rent shoes there. All you need to bring is your student id and yourself. Enjoy some heart racing moments!

1.name: Alton Baker
1.description: Spend the day leisurely walking or biking through the vast park that is Alton Baker, which spans from Eugene, Springfield, Coburg, and the Valley River areas. The paths in Alton Baker include paved bike paths as well as running and walking paths.

1.name: Skinner Butte Viewpoint
1.description: Go star gazing or check out the lights of the city of Eugene at the top of Skinner's Butte.

1.name: Garden at Henricks Park
1.description: Spend some time tending to the plants or walking the trails in Henricks Park. There is a group of regular volunteers that meet on Tuesdays from 9am - 12pm on the main lawn. Feel free to join them!
1.address: Summit Ave &, Skyline Blvd, Eugene, OR 97403

1.name: Stroll around the Eugene Saturday Market
1.description: Every Saturday rain or shine visit the Saturday Market from 10am-4pm.
1.address: 8th Ave & Oak Street (April - November) and Lane Events Center (December - March)

1.name: Run the Ridgeline Trail
1.description: Are you an avid runner? Take a shot running this [12 mile, 2,188 feet elevation gain] hike/running trail.

1.name: Run through South Amazon Running Trail
1.description: This is a flat-grade trail compromised of cedar chips, so it is easy on the knees. It is a 3.5 mile loop that can be made longer when connected to the North Trail.

1.name: Play disk golf at the Alton Baker Disk Golf Course
1.description: This course has 18 holes. No disks? No problem! You can rent them on sight.

1.name: Skatepark
1.description: Go skating at Amazom Park it consists of a small snake run into a shallow bowl with a small extension added on to the bowl.

1.name: Emerald Valley EMX
1.description: The track is free and open to the public Thursday through Sunday from 8 a.m. until sunset. The track offers a safety pro gate, paved corners, paved starting hill, soil tacked track, 10 shoot staging area, long roll out for finish line, fenced facility, ample parking and vendor space available.

1.name: Go swimming
1.description: Go swimming this summer at Amazon Pool. Open from May-October Features a beginner pool, sand play area, hot tub, 50-meter by 25-yard pool, 5-meter diving tower and a multipurpose pool with interactive play features including a water slide. Accessible to people with disabilities.

1.name: Go ice skating
1.description: Bring some ice skates or rent when you get there! This rink is a family friendly, fun area to spend the day no matter the weather.

2.name: Willamette Pass Ski Resort
2.description: Willamette Pass Resort offers access to 555 acres of lift-served trails perfect for skiing, cross country skiing, or even snow shoeing! The perfect snow activity, dedicate an entire day towards this activity, but you can participate in the adventure as long/short as you want. Never skiied or snowboarded before? They offer lessons!
2.isClear: Yes, although this is a winter only activity
2.isRain: No, either snow or blue skies, there is no in-between on this one.
2.address: 27501 Hwy 58, Mile Marker 62, Crescent Lake, OR 97733

2.name: Fern Ridge Reserviour
2.description: Fern Ridge Reservoir is an amazing lake for boaters throughout the Willamette Valley and beyond. It is considered one of the best sailing lakes in the Northwest! Enjoy sailing on a gusty day.
2.address: Fern Ridge Lake, 26647 OR-126, Veneta, OR 97487

2.name: Whale Watching
2.description: No matter what time of year, you might see whales along the Oregon Coast. From mid-December to mid-January you can see the gray whales on their way down to Mexico. In late March through early June you could catch them on their way back up to Alaska. Finally, summer and fall bring these whales close to the shore to feed.

2.name: Star Gazing
2.description: In the midst of a rocky lava landscape, discover this memorable monument. This historical observatory, built of lava rock, offers stunning panoramic views of Cascade Mountain peaks.

2.name: Sand boarding on the Oregon Dunes
2.description: Cruise down the Oregon Dunes for a uniquely exhilerating experience!

2.name: Visit the Sea Lion Caves
2.description: Walk deep into a sea lion cave to get a first hand glance of these amazing creatures.

2.name: Fly a Kite at the South Jetty in Florence
2.description: Grab or rent a kite and head over to the South Jetty for a great time - the winds are there, so fly away!
2.address: South Jetty (South Beach State Park), Newport, OR 97365

2.name: Kite Surfing
2.description: Are you a die-hard kite surfer? Look no further than the Oregon Coast for your next adventure. We've checked the wind, you're good to go!

2.name: Surfing
2.description: Put on that wet suit! We've got a local surf spot for you.
2.address: South Jetty (South Beach State Park), Newport, OR 97365

2.name: Mountain Biking
2.description: Grab your bike and hit some world renowned mountain biking trails in Oakridge.
2.isRain: Yes but be careful. This trail could be slippery when wet.

2.name: Bike through the covered bridges scenic bikeway
2.description: Totaling 36 miles, this loop can be as hard or as easy as you want. Grab your bike and check out some bridges!

2.name: Dune Buggy Tour
2.description: Adventure through the Oregon Dunes with a Dune Buggy Tour! Please note that this adventure is not free.

2.name: Golfing at the Oregon Coast
2.description: Enjoy a trip golfing at the Oregon Coast.

2.name: Waldo Lake Sno-Park
2.description: Sno-Park permit required - Waldo Lake Road is a shared snowmobile/ski route, but snowmobiles are not permitted on other nordic trails in this area.
2.address: Junction at Milepost 63 on Hwy 58, proceed 6 miles (10 km) to Waldo Lake Recreation Area, Oakridge, OR 97463

2.name: Snowshoe to Salt Creek Falls
2.description: Come see Oregon's second highest waterfall this winter! All you need is some warm clothes and some snowshoes.
2.address: Hwy 58, east of milepost 58, Salt Creek Falls Observation Site, Oakridge, OR 97463

2.name: Cross Country Ski at Gold-Lake Sno-Park
2.description: Enjoy a relaxing, brisk, and fun day cross country skiing!

2.name: McCredie Hot Springs
2.description: Soak up some luxurious heat during the cold months in this gorgeous hot spring.
2.address: 11 miles on Hwy 58, Just past Blue Pool Campground, Oakridge, OR 97463

2.name: Blue River Lake
2.description: Enjoy a refreshing dip in Blue River Lake during Oregon's summer months

2.name: Lounge on the beach
2.description: Enjoy a relaxing day lounging on the beach or talking a nice walk along the sand
2.address: Hwy 101, 13.7 miles (23.7 km) north of Florence, Florence, OR 97439

2.name: Siltcoos River Trail
2.description: The Siltcoos River Trail leads from Siltcoos Lake to the Pacific Ocean. This six-mile round-trip paddle allows you to travel down to the Pacific Ocean and back to Siltcoos Lake. Check the tide-tables first — if you time it properly, you can go downstream with the falling tide and then come back upstream on the rising tide — making for an easy paddle.

2.name: Kayak on Dexter Reservoir
2.description: Kayak for a long as you'd like on this beautiful lake.

2.name: Elk Hiking Trail
2.description: 1.6 mile 13ft elevation gain, only takes 30 minutes to complete. Great for a quick, relaxing day.

2.name: Tamolitch Blue Pool via McKenzie River Trail
2.description: This 3.6 mile and 285ft elevation gain hike has stunningly rewarding views. Enjoy your hike to, as the name says, a really blue pool! It should take you about 1 h and 30 minutes to complete.

2.name: Castle Rock Trail
2.description: This 8.6 mile, 2,106ft elevation gain hike is perfect for a sunny day. With good visibility, you'll get some stellar views.

2.name: Trestle Creek Falls Loop
2.description: Nice 4.8 mile, 1,325 feet elevation gain loop that includes views of a creek and waterfall
